description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly organised Administrator / PA to join our multi-disciplinary team. The safeguarding children and maternity team provide advice and guidance to staff members across the Trust in all matters relating to the safeguarding of children and vulnerable families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is multi faceted and no two days are the same. To ensure successful delivery of the core services and requirements the post holder should have effective time management skills and experience of working to meet targets within a set deadline. They should also have experience of handling highly sensitive information whilst ensuring that all internal systems and the information contained within them are managed effectively and in-line with local processes. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be a point of contact for staff and external agencies, providing advice in a professional and confidential manner. Excellent communication skills and attention to detail, both written and oral, are both essential criteria for the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide PA support to the Head of Nursing and Lead Nurse for safeguarding children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support will be given for developmental opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
